<!--
If this is the customized commands file, you can edit it to customize menu commands and toolbars. Then restart the program.
	To add a command to a toolbar, add command's XML element to the toolbar's XML element.
	To reset everything, delete this file. To reset some toolbars, delete all commands in their XML elements.
If this is the default commands file, please don't edit/delete it.

Most command names are like default menu item text, with _ instead of space and without ....
	For example, if text in menu is "Open file...", command is Open_file.
	The program prints all available command names if this file contains unknown commands. The same for toolbar names.

Command XML attributes:
color - text color. Value: .NET color name or #RRGGBB or #RGB.
text - menu item text. Also button text, if btext not specified. Insert _ before Alt-underlined character.
image - image file. Can be xaml, png or other format supported by WPF. Path can start with %EnvVariable% or %AFolders.Folder%.
keys - keyboard or/and mouse shortcut(s), like "Ctrl+E, Shift+M-click". Mouse can be: Click, D-click, R-click, M-click, Wheel.

These attributes are used only for toolbar buttons:
separator - add separator before. Value: none.
hide - overflow mode. Value: always, never, asNeeded (default).
imageAt - show image + text; image at this side. Value: left, top, right, bottom. For submenu-items always left.
btext - button text.

All attributes are optional. The Example command contains all.
<Example color="green" text="Text1" image="c:\m\n.png" keys="Ctrl+H" separator="1" hide="1" imageAt="left" btext="Text2"/>
-->
